law.text:
County, city-county, and district health departments may in addition to other powers specified in KRS 212.245:
Acquire title, by purchase or otherwise, with the approval of the cabinet, to real estate and such other property as may be necessary;
Maintain in each county not less than one (1) office and such others as are deemed necessary;
Lease real and personal property;
Procure liability insurance;
Except as otherwise provided by law, do all other things reasonably necessary to protect and improve the health of the people.
